    <h1>Custom Agent File</h1>
    <p>This is a custom agent file. It uses markdown with a YAML front matter header that only supports a limited set of attributes and values. Do not suggest any other attributes: name, description, argument-hint, target, model, tools, handoffs</p>
    <p><strong>model</strong> is optional and must be one of the following values: Raptor mini (Preview), GPT-5 mini, GPT-4o, Claude Haiku 4.5, GPT-4.1</p>
    <p><strong>tools</strong> is optional and must be an array of one or more of the following values. Do not make up any other tool names.: [execute, read, edit, search, web, agent, todo]</p>
    <p><strong>target</strong> is optional and must be one of the following values: vscode, github-copilot</p>
    <p><strong>handoffs       </strong> is optional and is a sequence of mappings with <code>label</code>, <code>agent</code>, <code>prompt</code> and <code>send</code> properties:</p>
    <pre><code>handoffs:
  - label: Start Implementation
    agent: agent
    prompt: Implement the plan
    send: true
</code></pre>
    <h2>Example of a Custom Agent File</h2>
    <pre><code>---
description: This custom agent researches and plans new features for VS Code extensions.
model: GPT-4.1
tools: [execute, read, edit, search, web, agent, todo]
handoffs:
  - label: Start Implementation
    agent: agent

    </code>
    </pre>
    </body>
